The Limpopo branch of the South African Institute of Civil Engineering (Saice) will host a golf day at Polokwane Golf Club on 18 November and teams are encouraged to enter as soon as possible to avoid disappointment. Organiser Louise van der Linde said it promises to be a day filled with not only furious competition but also fun and big prizes up for grabs. The competition will be hosted in four ball alliance format and the closing date for entries is next Thursday, 10 November. Entry fees are R1 000 per person or R4 000 for a company package. Several sponsorships of holes are also available. For information and entries contact Van der Linde on 079 081 2419 or email on louise.saicelimpopo@gmail.com. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com